==English==
===Etymology===
From [[w:Christiaan Huygens|Christiaan Huygens]], Dutch physicist
===Noun phrase===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Huygens' principle'''
#{{physics}} the [[assumption]] that each point on a [[wavefront]] may be regarded as a [[source]] of [[secondary]] [[wave]]s and that the position of the wavefront at a later time is determined by the [[envelope]] of these secondary waves; proposed in order to explain the fact that [[light]] travels in a [[straight line]] and casts [[sharp]] [[shadow]]s
